column5: I'm sure it's where you think.Let's get Brian going. I've been waiting for two weeks lol. Let's try for saturday.Most times I miss when he's heading out:wallbash:.
WTG, Bubba! You did good!
Can almost taste the meal it looks so good! Nicely done!
Nicely done Sir!

Havent eaten a fresh water fish in about 9 or so years,I thought it was time to have one. Crappie is all I wanted,and crappie is all I got.  Walked out,found the weeds,and drilled back til I was on the edge of them.    Start fishing. Didnt take long and the first was up out of the hole.    A few minutes later,another.    Then this one,going close to 12 inches,smashed the small jig.    It was a good bite.  14 total for the few hours I was out,    Playing with macro again.    Kept 4 to eat for lunch.It was delis.
That's a nice day of fishing! Dems crappies are damn delicious too.
Nice. I am taking the boy out tomorrow. Is that Simcoe?
wow, that has me itching to get out. Thanks for the report
why was it I drove miles for the same thing...lol nice going
Oh man, great fishing.    Oh and the GULP sponsorship check is in the mail.
I'm thinking of going out next Saturday.
Very nice Brian!!  You guys are really giving me the fever.  Think I'm taking one of my ice rods down to the aquarium...our fish Sharkey is about 12" now, lol!
Nice! Can't wait to get into some of my own
You were leaving as I was heading in. Good feast I'd say!!!!!
Some nice looking crappies B   and that plate shot looks mint
Thanks all.   LOL Jeremy.  That stuff stinks to all heaven,but it sure works.    Give a shout Rob,if you do.     Where were ya Dave?   MAYBE IT,S THE FUMES FROM YOUR HAND WARMER
Longterm forecast is sketchy for Saturday. I hope it improves as the week goes on.
Right on Brian!  4 slabs like that size is a perfect meal!
Good haul Brian have you tried meal worms up North they are a really good bait for crappie down here when it gets cold.    Art
Nice size on them too! You've got me itching for crappies just a little bit now.
very nice! No crappie for me, only walleye.
Awesome catch Brian !!!! Sure was a crappie day your right !!!!
nice. i might be in for saturday if that is where i think it is.
Way to go B     Them looks darn tasty
Good job B
Would love to get into to some slabs like that. Something about enticing crappie into hitting a jig that I love.  Can only find stunted minitaure crappie in my neck of the woods.
Way to go bro, just saw your thread. You see any them down the hole looking for me  Love to get out after some of those babies. Man that plate looks DELISH
NO fish is better then Crappie when it comes to a FISH FRY....
Good job B!  looks tasty.  how deep were they?
